  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q063.a004.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">strong_textual_inference</data>
  <data key="d17">As stated above ( II-II:60:1 ), judgment is an act of justice , in as much as the judge restores to the equality of justice , those things which may cause an opposite inequality. Now respect of persons involves a certain</data>
  <data key="d18">reviewed_doctrinal</data>
</edge>
