  <data key="d16">strong_textual_inference</data>
  <data key="d17">According to the Philosopher (Ethic. i, 3), "we must not expect to find certitude equally in every matter." For in human acts , on which judgments are passed and evidence required, it is impossible to have demonstrative certitude , because they a about things</data>
