  <data key="d15">st.ii-ii.q077.a001.resp</data>
  <data key="d16">strong_textual_inference</data>
  <data key="d17">It is altogether sinful to have recourse to deceit in order to sell a thing for more than its just price, because this is to deceive one's neighbor so as to injure him. Hence Tully says (De Offic. iii, 15): "Contracts should be entirely free from double-dealing: t</data>
